As early as April 1941, Camus had been working on the novel, as evidenced in his diaries in which he wrote down a few ideas on "the redeeming plague".<ref>Camus, Albert, ''Carnets I, Mai 1935 - février 1942'', Paris, Gallimard, 2013, 234 p. ({{ISBN|978-2-07045404-4}}), p.204</ref> On March 13, 1942, he informed [[André Malraux]] that he was writing "a novel on the plague", adding  "Said like that it might sound strange, […] but this subject seems so natural to me."<ref>Camus, Albert, Malraux, André, ''Albert Camus, André Malraux, Correspondance 1941–1959'', Paris, Gallimard, 2016, 152 p. ({{ISBN|978-2-07-014690-1}}), p.42</ref>

